22/05/2005
VARNA, Bulgaria -- Top leaders of Balkan nations joined UNESCO and Council of Europe officials in Varna to discuss measures for preservation and promotion of the region's rich cultural heritage.
In attendance were the presidents of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Macedonia, Montenegro and Turkey, as well as the culture ministers of Romania and Serbia.
The two-day meeting, which began Friday (20 May), was seen as a major effort towards enhancing regional institutional co-operation.
(24 Chasa, bTV, PBS BiH, ANA, TurkishPress.com - 21/05/05)
